============================================================================

1. v4 nominal: I_b = 2.0 nA, V0 = 50.0 kV, L = 100.0 mm
   σ_LJ (Jansen, pencil-beam K=1.587) = 7.13 nm  (FW50)
   σ_LJ_rms = FW50/1.18              = 6.04 nm
   Band (K∈[1.2,2.0], g∈[1,1.5]): [5.39, 13.47] nm FW50  = [4.57, 11.41] nm RMS

2. IMS Nano MBMW calibration anchor:
   At I=0.5 nA, L=50 mm, V0=50 kV → σ_LJ_pred = 1.000 nm
   Published total placement <2 nm; LJ attribution ~1 nm → consistent

3. Boersch energy spread at v4 nominal:
   ΔE = 1.347 eV FW50
   Chromatic aberration coeff C_c ≈ 50 μm (well-designed EBL column):
   σ_B ≈ (ΔE/V0) × C_c = (1.347/50000) × 50 μm = 1.35 nm

